🧠 What is MongoDB?

**MongoDB** is a **NoSQL database** that stores data in **JSON-like format**.

📌 Data is stored as **documents**
📌 Flexible schema
📌 Highly scalable

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 SQL vs MongoDB

| SQL Database      | MongoDB         |
| ----------------- | --------------- |
| Tables            | Collections     |
| Rows              | Documents       |
| Fixed schema      | Flexible schema |
| MySQL, PostgreSQL | MongoDB         |

---

🔷 MongoDB Structure

```text
Database
   ↓
Collection
   ↓
Document (JSON)
```

---

🔷 Example Document

```json
{
  "name": "Saakshi",
  "age": 22,
  "skills": ["JavaScript", "React"]
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Why MongoDB?

✔ Flexible data storage
✔ Easy to scale
✔ Fast performance
✔ Perfect for full stack apps

---

🔷 What is Mongoose?

**Mongoose** is a **Node.js library (ODM)** for MongoDB.

👉 Helps to:

✔ Define schema
✔ Validate data
✔ Interact with database easily

---

🔷 Install Mongoose

```bash
npm install mongoose
```

---

🔷 Connect MongoDB with Node.js

```javascript
const mongoose = require("mongoose");

mongoose.connect("mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/mydb")
  .then(() => console.log("Connected to MongoDB"))
  .catch(err => console.error(err));
```

---

🔷 Create Schema

```javascript
const userSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  name: String,
  age: Number
});
```

---

🔷 Create Model

```javascript
const User = mongoose.model("User", userSchema);
```

---

🔷 Insert Data

```javascript
const user = new User({
  name: "Saakshi",
  age: 22
});

user.save();
```

---

🔷 Fetch Data

```javascript
User.find().then(users => console.log(users));
```

---

🔷 Update Data

```javascript
User.updateOne({ name: "Saakshi" }, { age: 23 });
```

---

🔷 Delete Data

```javascript
User.deleteOne({ name: "Saakshi" });
```

---

🔷 CRUD Operations

| Operation | Method      |
| --------- | ----------- |
| Create    | save()      |
| Read      | find()      |
| Update    | updateOne() |
| Delete    | deleteOne() |

---

🔷 Mongoose vs MongoDB

| MongoDB       | Mongoose            |
| ------------- | ------------------- |
| Raw database  | ODM library         |
| Flexible      | Structured schema   |
| No validation | Built-in validation |

